WEBVTT

00:01.171 --> 00:02.622
<i>So here's what you missed
on Glee:</i>

00:02.706 --> 00:04.207
<i>The glee club's
getting ready for Nationals,</i>

00:04.258 --> 00:05.792
<i>and Quinn's getting ready
to be prom queen.</i>

00:05.876 --> 00:07.627
We need to get elected
for prom king and queen.

00:07.695 --> 00:08.594
It's the ultimate
status symbol.

00:08.679 --> 00:09.912
<i>Kurt had to leave McKinley</i>

00:09.963 --> 00:10.963
<i>because Karofsky
threatened him...</i>

00:11.031 --> 00:12.081
I can't expel a kid
for shoving.

00:12.132 --> 00:13.099
He'll just say, "I didn't mean

00:13.183 --> 00:14.500
to shove that kid.
I tripped."

00:14.568 --> 00:16.052
Excuse works like a charm.
I use it all the time.

00:16.103 --> 00:17.520
<i>But at least he's got
Blaine and the Warblers,</i>

00:17.587 --> 00:19.588
<i>who just lost at Regionals
to the New Directions!</i>

00:19.640 --> 00:21.107
We got each other
out of all this.

00:21.191 --> 00:23.192
That beats a lousy trophy,
don't you think?

00:23.260 --> 00:24.760
<i>Santana's got it bad
for Brittany...</i>

00:24.812 --> 00:26.062
This relationship
is really confusing for me.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.697
Breakfast is confusing for you.

00:27.765 --> 00:30.066
Well, sometimes it's sweet
and sometimes it's salty.

00:30.117 --> 00:32.735
Like, what if I have eggs
for dinner, then what is it?

00:32.786 --> 00:34.237
<i>Will's sort of always
had it bad for Emma,</i>

00:34.288 --> 00:35.538
<i>but lately she's gotten
super crazy</i>

00:35.605 --> 00:36.739
<i>with the cleaning fruit
and stuff.</i>

00:36.790 --> 00:38.458
<i>I'm not following.
Like, seriously crazy.</i>

00:38.542 --> 00:41.828
One day, you're going to find
a way to beat this thing.

00:41.912 --> 00:44.030
<i>And that's what you missed
on Glee.</i>

00:45.666 --> 00:46.799
All right, guys.

00:46.884 --> 00:48.468
Nationals are just
a few weeks away,

00:48.552 --> 00:50.136
and it's time to bear down.

00:50.220 --> 00:53.055
Now, your singing at Regionals
was amazing, but your dancing...

00:54.675 --> 00:56.342
It's booty camp time.

00:56.427 --> 00:57.510
Booty!
So let's get it going.

00:57.594 --> 00:59.011
Five, six, seven, eight.

01:00.797 --> 01:02.231
Push yourselves, guys.

01:02.299 --> 01:03.466
Vocal Adrenaline
takes no prisoners.

01:04.685 --> 01:06.635
Oh! I'm so sorry.

01:06.687 --> 01:07.937
Are you okay?

01:07.988 --> 01:09.071
I'm bleeding.

01:09.139 --> 01:10.773
Let's get you to a doctor.

01:13.026 --> 01:14.694
My dad's will be here
in 15 minutes.

01:14.778 --> 01:16.162
You don't have to stay, Finn.

01:16.246 --> 01:18.814
No, I want to wait
and hear what the doctor says.

01:18.866 --> 01:20.366
I feel terrible.

01:20.451 --> 01:23.419
Won't Quinn be mad at you
sitting vigil at my bedside?

01:23.487 --> 01:24.837
Well, I'm standing,

01:24.922 --> 01:27.707
and-and she'd understand
how awful I feel

01:27.775 --> 01:29.008
even if it's not broken.

01:29.092 --> 01:30.009
It's broken.

01:31.595 --> 01:33.596
Well, I knew
I was a bad dancer,

01:33.663 --> 01:35.264
but I never thought
my dancing was dangerous.

01:35.332 --> 01:37.666
It's a clean break, so
I-I won't have to set it.

01:37.718 --> 01:39.835
Considering your
deviated septum,

01:39.887 --> 01:42.004
I'd consider this a
terrific opportunity

01:42.055 --> 01:43.656
for a little vanity adjustment.

01:43.724 --> 01:45.892
Are you suggesting
that I get a nose job?

01:45.976 --> 01:47.193
You're 16, right?

01:47.277 --> 01:49.178
That's when I gave
my daughters theirs.

01:49.246 --> 01:50.980
It's like a right of
passage for Jewish girls.

01:51.031 --> 01:54.150
First of all, I like how I look.

01:54.201 --> 01:56.352
She your girlfriend?

01:56.420 --> 01:57.686
No.

01:57.738 --> 01:59.522
What does your
girlfriend look like?

01:59.573 --> 02:02.375
Okay, and second of all,
I don't want to do anything

02:02.459 --> 02:03.759
that's going to affect my voice.

02:03.827 --> 02:04.961
My Broadway career
depends on it.

02:05.028 --> 02:06.546
Yeah, we got a big show choir

02:06.630 --> 02:07.630
competition coming up,
and Rachel's

02:07.697 --> 02:08.697
kind of our best singer.

02:08.749 --> 02:09.749
Doesn't impact the voice.

02:09.833 --> 02:10.917
That's just a myth.

02:11.001 --> 02:12.835
The fact is, opening
up that septum

02:12.886 --> 02:15.538
might allow you to take
in more air per breath,

02:15.589 --> 02:17.423
which means bigger
belts on you high notes.

02:17.508 --> 02:19.708
But Barbra...

02:19.760 --> 02:22.728
Is great.
She's also one in a million.

02:24.731 --> 02:27.383
The fact is, if you really
want to be an actress,

02:27.434 --> 02:29.218
you might want to consider
looking and sounding

02:29.269 --> 02:30.736
the best that you can.

02:30.821 --> 02:33.272
I got an appointment
open next week.

02:33.357 --> 02:35.525
Can I sign you up?

02:36.814 --> 02:39.144
Sync by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

02:39.329 --> 02:41.747
Oh my God,
you're getting a nose job.

02:41.831 --> 02:44.283
I'm considering having
a minor procedure

02:44.367 --> 02:45.501
to repair my deviated septum.

02:45.568 --> 02:47.219
So, a nose job.

02:47.287 --> 02:50.172
Look, I'm... I'm happy
with the way that I look, okay?

02:50.239 --> 02:51.790
And I've embraced my nose.

02:51.875 --> 02:55.911
But let's say I wanted to have
a slightly more demure nose.

02:55.962 --> 02:58.097
Like Quinn's, for example.

02:58.181 --> 03:01.100
I-I would never change
my appearance for vanity,

03:01.184 --> 03:03.302
but, I mean, the doctor said

03:03.386 --> 03:05.320
that it could possibly
improve my talent,

03:05.388 --> 03:07.689
which would help us
all for Nationals.

03:07.757 --> 03:10.258
Possibly?
What about the risks?

03:10.310 --> 03:12.194
Your voice is amazing
as is, Rachel.

03:12.261 --> 03:13.445
Hold up.

03:13.530 --> 03:15.280
Could we all just
get real here for a second?

03:15.365 --> 03:17.766
I hear that Rachel's got
a bit of a schnoz.

03:17.817 --> 03:19.985
I mean, I wouldn't know
because, like Medusa, I try

03:20.070 --> 03:21.353
to avoid eye contact with her.

03:21.421 --> 03:22.771
But can we all just stop

03:22.822 --> 03:24.490
lying about how
there aren't things

03:24.574 --> 03:25.958
that we wouldn't change
about ourselves?

03:26.042 --> 03:29.128
I mean, I'm sure that Sam's been
at the doctor's office

03:29.212 --> 03:31.080
and rifled through pamphlets
on mouth reduction.

03:31.131 --> 03:32.798
I'll bet Artie's thought
about getting his legs removed

03:32.882 --> 03:34.083
since he's not really
using them anyways.

03:34.134 --> 03:36.418
And I'm definitely sure
that Tina's looked

03:36.469 --> 03:37.786
into getting an eye de-slanting.

03:37.837 --> 03:38.804
That's extraordinarily racist.

03:38.888 --> 03:40.122
I'm keepin' it real.

03:40.173 --> 03:41.974
Sorry, Santana.
I'm a beautiful person.

03:42.058 --> 03:44.626
I'm in love with myself, and I
would never change a thing.

03:44.677 --> 03:47.179
Is that why you're wearing
blue contacts today, Tina?

03:47.263 --> 03:49.565
Self-hating Asian.

03:49.632 --> 03:50.799
Not many Asian sex symbols,
Mike.

03:50.850 --> 03:52.434
I'm just trying to be in fashion

03:52.485 --> 03:54.269
and mirror what I see
in the magazines.

03:54.320 --> 03:55.988
My dancing kind of bothers me.

03:56.072 --> 04:00.025
Uh, it almost killed Rachel,
but I like the way I look.

04:00.110 --> 04:01.443
Oh, please.

04:01.494 --> 04:03.662
You have weird, puffy
pyramid nipples.

04:03.746 --> 04:05.247
They look like they're
filled with custard,

04:05.314 --> 04:06.698
or you could dust them

04:06.783 --> 04:08.200
with powdered sugar
and they could pass

04:08.284 --> 04:10.702
for some sort of dessert.

04:10.787 --> 04:13.705
Look, maybe Rachel's fine
with having an enormous beak.

04:13.790 --> 04:16.208
Maybe she needs it to crack
hard seeds. All I'm saying

04:16.291 --> 04:17.793
is that if you look
in the mirror

04:17.844 --> 04:19.928
and you don't like what you see,
you should change it.

04:19.995 --> 04:21.430
Whoa, guys.

04:21.497 --> 04:23.265
I'm really shocked
at what I'm hearing here.

04:23.332 --> 04:25.317
It goes against everything
the glee club stands for.

04:25.385 --> 04:28.437
I'm telling you, the thing
you would most like to change

04:28.504 --> 04:31.023
about yourself is the most
interesting part of you.

04:31.107 --> 04:32.975
Well, maybe,
but at this school,

04:33.026 --> 04:34.726
the thing
that makes you different

04:34.811 --> 04:36.512
is the thing people use
to crush your spirit.

04:44.037 --> 04:45.821
Rachel's a beautiful girl.

04:45.872 --> 04:47.522
She doesn't need a nose job.

04:47.574 --> 04:50.358
Saying that she's doing it
to enrich her talent is just

04:50.410 --> 04:52.161
a convenient excuse
to deal with the fact

04:52.212 --> 04:53.862
that she's insecure
about how she looks.

04:53.913 --> 04:56.198
Most of the adults we know
have trouble embracing

04:56.249 --> 04:58.133
their eccentricities, so
how can we expect kids to?

04:58.201 --> 05:00.385
Well, then, it should be
our job to help them.

05:00.470 --> 05:01.703
I don't want my legacy
as a teacher

05:01.754 --> 05:05.057
to be conjugated verbs
and Glee Club trophies.

05:05.141 --> 05:06.875
I want to help them
love themselves

05:06.926 --> 05:09.311
for who they are,
warts and all--

05:09.378 --> 05:11.013
Especially warts.

05:11.064 --> 05:12.681
How long do we have
to do this for?

05:12.732 --> 05:14.149
Until they're all clean.

05:14.217 --> 05:16.885
I mean, I'm really enjoying
helping you with your OCD.

05:16.936 --> 05:19.188
Do you know what? I really
don't like that term, really.

05:19.239 --> 05:20.939
It sounds way too
scientific and serious.

05:21.024 --> 05:23.225
I really prefer "neat
freak" or "cleanybug."

05:23.276 --> 05:25.110
But, Will, I really
have to tell you,

05:25.195 --> 05:28.247
I'm so appreciative
of all your help.

05:28.331 --> 05:29.915
Really, I have so
much more free time

05:29.999 --> 05:32.084
now that there are four hands
polishing all of my fruit.

05:32.168 --> 05:34.119
I'm really glad...

05:34.204 --> 05:35.370
but shouldn't we
be figuring out

05:35.421 --> 05:36.505
some techniques you can use

05:36.572 --> 05:38.406
to eat your food
without scrubbing it?

05:38.458 --> 05:40.575
You mean with germs and
pesticides all over it?

05:40.627 --> 05:44.463
No, I mean, really deal
with your issues on this stuff.

05:44.547 --> 05:47.182
Will, I've tried, you know,

05:47.250 --> 05:49.417
and I... I may not have
been born this way,

05:49.469 --> 05:51.586
but this is my lot in life.

05:51.638 --> 05:54.189
There's nothing I
can do about it.

05:54.257 --> 05:56.642
Thank you.

05:56.726 --> 05:58.560
What for?

05:58.611 --> 06:00.696
I know how I'm going
to get the kids

06:00.763 --> 06:02.731
to accept what
their differences are--

06:02.782 --> 06:04.983
By using their two
favorite teachers:

06:05.051 --> 06:08.237
Me and Gaga...

06:08.288 --> 06:10.205
but I'm going
to need your help.

06:14.210 --> 06:15.994
<i>I should be prom queen
at this school.</i>

06:16.079 --> 06:17.579
<i>If I were prom queen,</i>

06:17.630 --> 06:19.381
<i>I could get Brittany to drop
the four-eyed loser</i>

06:19.448 --> 06:21.550
<i>and go for the real queen.</i>

06:21.617 --> 06:23.001
<i>She's so gullible,
I could convince her</i>

06:23.086 --> 06:25.337
<i>that by royal decree,
I'd made her being with me</i>

06:25.421 --> 06:27.806
<i>the law of the land.</i>

06:27.890 --> 06:29.124
<i>That's never going to happen.</i>

06:29.175 --> 06:30.642
<i>I don't have the votes.</i>

06:30.727 --> 06:32.261
<i>Unless I could get
the jock block.</i>

06:32.312 --> 06:34.229
Jack Ryan, you've just boarded

06:34.297 --> 06:35.297
<i>the Red October.</i>

06:36.482 --> 06:37.316
Sean Connery.

06:39.135 --> 06:40.569
<i>And God knows Sam doesn't have</i>

06:40.636 --> 06:42.187
<i>the heat at this school yet.</i>

06:42.272 --> 06:44.139
<i>Hold on, there's someone
at this school</i>

06:44.190 --> 06:46.474
<i>who just might have
the juice...</i>

06:46.526 --> 06:47.576
<i>Dave Karofsky.</i>

06:50.079 --> 06:51.813
<i>Holy crap.</i>

06:53.649 --> 06:56.335
<i>I'm a closet lesbian
and a judgmental bitch,</i>

06:56.419 --> 06:59.288
I have awesome gaydar.

07:01.090 --> 07:03.658
You haven't asked us anything
about our New York trip.

07:03.710 --> 07:05.427
Is it because it's too painful?

07:05.494 --> 07:06.828
Yes, as a matter of fact,

07:06.879 --> 07:07.929
but while the New Directions!

07:07.997 --> 07:09.831
Are preparing
to perform at Nationals,

07:09.882 --> 07:12.334
the Warblers are preparing
to perform at a nursing home

07:12.385 --> 07:14.186
in a strip mall
next to a National Bank.

07:15.688 --> 07:16.938
But I'm so proud of you guys.

07:17.006 --> 07:18.506
We miss you so much.

07:18.558 --> 07:20.859
Isn't there any way you
could come back to McKinley?

07:20.943 --> 07:23.779
I told him, I would be all for
it if it wasn't for Karofsky.

07:24.981 --> 07:26.481
Wait, what did you just say?

07:26.532 --> 07:27.899
Kurt needs to be safe.

07:27.967 --> 07:29.684
Okay, can we please
change subject?

07:29.736 --> 07:31.320
<i>- I'm just saying...
- That's it.</i>

07:31.387 --> 07:34.456
<i>Kurt's the trick to winning
prom queen and getting Britt,</i>

07:34.523 --> 07:37.209
<i>not to mention totally boosting
our chances at Nationals.</i>

07:37.293 --> 07:40.295
<i>If I could get Kurt back,
I'd be a hero.</i>

07:40.363 --> 07:41.830
<i>Even Quinn and Finn
would vote for me.</i>

07:41.881 --> 07:43.332
<i>And the key?</i>

07:43.383 --> 07:44.249
<i>Karofsky.</i>

07:45.802 --> 07:47.102
I've got to gay-- Go.

07:47.170 --> 07:48.203
Go-- I've got to go.

07:52.308 --> 07:55.377
Um, why is Ms. Pillsbury here?

07:55.428 --> 07:57.062
She's helping us out
with this week's assignment.

07:57.146 --> 07:58.397
Now, this is the only club

07:58.464 --> 07:59.598
at school that is represented

07:59.682 --> 08:02.217
by just about every race,
religion,

08:02.285 --> 08:04.386
sexual orientation and clique,

08:04.437 --> 08:06.855
but many of you are still having
a hard time with acceptance.

08:06.906 --> 08:08.874
That's crazy, Mr. Shue.
We love each other.

08:08.941 --> 08:10.659
No, I won't deny that
you accept each other,

08:10.726 --> 08:12.911
but you don't
accept yourselves.

08:12.979 --> 08:14.663
This week's assignment
has two parts.

08:14.730 --> 08:17.449
I want all of you to sing
songs about accepting yourself

08:17.533 --> 08:21.286
for who you are-- The
best and the worst parts.

08:21.371 --> 08:23.255
What's the second part?
Well,

08:23.339 --> 08:24.790
we're going to do
a group number

08:24.874 --> 08:26.842
by the queen
of self-love--

08:26.909 --> 08:28.243
Gaga.

08:28.294 --> 08:30.128
We're going to perform

08:30.213 --> 08:32.631
her anthem to acceptance--
"Born This Way."

08:32.715 --> 08:35.015
Yes!

08:35.083 --> 08:38.720
Wait, wait, I still don't know
why Ms. Pillsbury is here.

08:38.770 --> 08:41.073
I'm here to help you with your
costumes for the big number.

08:41.140 --> 08:42.890
Each of you will be issued
a beautifully fitted

08:42.942 --> 08:44.592
white T-shirt.

08:44.644 --> 08:47.762
We will then use
this letter press...

08:47.814 --> 08:49.264
to write a word or a phrase

08:49.332 --> 08:50.899
that best describes
the thing about you

08:50.950 --> 08:52.150
that you're the most ashamed of

08:52.235 --> 08:54.069
or you'd like to
change but you can't

08:54.120 --> 08:56.604
because you were born that way,
which is super terrific. I want you

08:56.656 --> 08:58.606
to love those parts of you,
you know, embrace them,

08:58.658 --> 08:59.908
wear them on your
chest with pride.

08:59.959 --> 09:01.993
Can you give an example?

09:02.078 --> 09:03.578
Yeah.

09:03.629 --> 09:04.996
It's the big moment.

09:11.087 --> 09:12.104
Wow, Emma, I thought
the whole purpose

09:12.171 --> 09:13.422
of you doing this
was to write...

09:13.473 --> 09:16.892
Being a ginger has plagued me
my entire life.

09:16.959 --> 09:18.593
People say
that I smell like copper,

09:18.644 --> 09:20.762
I can get a sunburn
indoors at night,

09:20.813 --> 09:23.131
and according to recent legend,
I have no soul,

09:23.199 --> 09:24.266
but I'm here to say
that this very curse

09:24.317 --> 09:26.268
is what makes me unique.

09:26.319 --> 09:28.186
Children,

09:28.271 --> 09:30.739
I claim my gingerhood
before you today.

09:32.475 --> 09:34.659
I was born this way.

09:34.744 --> 09:35.977
Hooray.

09:36.028 --> 09:37.279
Hooray!

09:37.330 --> 09:38.530
Hooray!

